        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 24 at 2:40AM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 240 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Idabel, or 23 miles northeast of Clarksville, moving east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Idabel, Broken Bow, Haworth, Garvin, Harris, Holly Creek, Bokhoma,
Goodwater, Moon, Oak Hill, America, Shinewell, Eagletown, Tom,
Bryarly, Cerrogordo, Golden and West Line.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
